lass=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">März 29, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104ots1665702620497.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ots1665702620497.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ots1665702620497.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"ots1665702620497\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Define a constant name and value.</p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"ots1665702620497__topic_d93059e1_d93060e1_d93061e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ots1665702620497__p_d93062e1_d93063e1_d93064e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">#define</span>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Constant</var> { <code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code> } <var class=\"keyword varname\">Expression</var>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ots1665702620497__section_zyb_pnb_lwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1063026e72\">Parameters</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"ots1665702620497__ul_ojy_pnb_lwb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ots1665702620497__li_d36431e1_d36432e1_d36433e1\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">Constant</var>—name of the\n               constant</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ots1665702620497__li_d36434e1_d36435e1_d36436e1\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">Expression</var>—expression that\n               evaluates to a constant value</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ots1665702620497__section_f5p_qnb_lwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1063026e91\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ots1665702620497__p_d93077e1_d93078e1_d93079e1\">The <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">#define</span> directive defines a\n            constant name and value during compilation for the current scope. For example, a\n            constant declared within a scope block (initiated by a <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">#startdefine</span>\n            directive) will be defined for the rest of the block until the corresponding\n               <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">#enddefine</span> statement.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ots1665702620497__p_d93080e1_d93081e1_d93082e1\">You can use constants as operands in expressions in\n            ProcScript by placing the name of the constant between angle brackets\n               (<code class=\"ph codeph\">&lt;&gt;</code>). When a component is compiled, the compiler replaces each\n            reference to a constant by the expression that has been defined for that constant.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ots1665702620497__p_d93083e1_d93084e1_d93085e1\">To define global constants, define them in a\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">DEFPARAM</code> IncludeScript. If they are defined in the IncludeScript\n            library called SYSTEM_LIBRARY, they are available to all your Uniface applications.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ots1665702620497__section_gyl_snb_lwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle exampletitle\" id=\"ots1665702620497__p_d93086e1_d93087e1_d93088e1\"> Example: Defining a\n            Constant </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ots1665702620497__p_d93089e1_d93090e1_d93091e1\">The following example defines a constant\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">MYCONSTANT</code> with the text <code class=\"ph codeph\">I'm defined</code>. If the\n            constant exists, the compiler generates a warning with the text of\n               <samp class=\"ph systemoutput sysout\">MYCONSTANT</samp>:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"ots1665702620497__pre_zzx_tnb_lwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">#define MYCONSTANT = I'm defined\n#ifdefined MYCONSTANT\n #warning &lt;MYCONSTANT&gt;\n#endif</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ots1665702620497__p_d93092e1_d93093e1_d93094e1\">This results, after compilation, in the following\n            message in the message frame:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"ots1665702620497__pre_b1y_tnb_lwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">warning: 1000 - I'm defined</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qzg1665702620270.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Constants</a><p>A constant is a value that remains unchanged during the course of code execution.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/unu1665702620895.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>#startdefine</a><p>Declares the scope of precompiler constant declarations (#define's)</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ktw1665702620584.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>#undefine</a><p>Undefine a constant for the scope of the constant declaration.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cew1665702621348.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>#ifdefined</a><p>Test if a constant has been defined.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/syc1665702621424.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>#ifundefined</a><p>Test if a constant has not been defined.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3615073\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3615073\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "#define Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated März 29, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Define a constant name and value. #define Constant { = } Expression Parameters Constant —name of the constant Expression —expression that evaluates to a constant value Description The #define directive defines a constant name and value during compilation for the current scope. For example, a constant declared within a scope block (initiated by a #startdefine directive) will be defined for the rest of the block until the corresponding #enddefine statement. You can use constants as operands in expressions in ProcScript by placing the name of the constant between angle brackets ( <> ). When a component is compiled, the compiler replaces each reference to a constant by the expression that has been defined for that constant. To define global constants, define them in a DEFPARAM IncludeScript. If they are defined in the IncludeScript library called SYSTEM_LIBRARY, they are available to all your Uniface applications. Example: Defining a Constant The following example defines a constant MYCONSTANT with the text I'm defined . If the constant exists, the compiler generates a warning with the text of MYCONSTANT : #define MYCONSTANT = I'm defined #ifdefined MYCONSTANT #warning <MYCONSTANT> #endif Copy This results, after compilation, in the following message in the message frame: warning: 1000 - I'm defined Copy Related Links Constants A constant is a value that remains unchanged during the course of code execution. #startdefine Declares the scope of precompiler constant declarations (#define's) #undefine Undefine a constant for the scope of the constant declaration. #ifdefined Test if a constant has been defined. #ifundefined Test if a constant has not been defined. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}